
[1]corner-stone

   CORNER-STONE, n. The stone which lies at the corner of two walls, and
   unites them; the principal stone, and especially the stone which forms
   the corner of the foundation of an edifice.

   Who laid the corner-stone thereof? Job 38.

   Christ himself being the chief corner-stone. Ephesians 2.
